  "texts": [
    "Such measurement is a fundamental process, necessary to gauge the AI's effectiveness in achieving its intended purpose.",
    "However, this method does not account for the AI's adaptability to novel situations; there is no generalization to unprecedented situations, neither of the program (narrow generalization) or the developer (broad generalization).",
    "Simply put, the AI operates within the confines of its programming, adept at handling specific tasks without venturing beyond the domain it was originally designed to operate in.",
    "In the latter approach, the AI system is appraised for its versatility and the ability to transcend the confines of specific tasks, demonstrating its utility across various domains, including those unforeseen by its creators.",
    "Evaluating such adaptability entails navigating a set of unique and intricate challenges."
  ],
